<item>
            <title>[SEC-240] Remove log4j.properties from release JARs</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-240</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;log4j.properties is included in acegi-security-1.0.0-RC2.jar. In certain circumstances this prevent log4j to load user&apos;s config file, instead log4j configured from log4j.properties from acegi-security-1.0.0-RC2.jar. While it can be workarounded by passing configuration filename property to log4j or by using log4j.xml it is undesirable anyway because it takes some time to understand why log4j doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
